Pricing pivot: feature unlock across 57 files (commit 3 of 8)

The heart of the strategic shift. Every product feature that was
gated behind Pro is now available to every paying tier
(Dream / Maker / Growth / Pro) plus the 14-day Trial. The only
remaining Pro-only surfaces are service-level: the white-glove
onboarding flow + the Pro onboarding-call banner. Anything that
delivers product value — COGS, integrations, reports, SKUs,
inventory, line-item ingest, profitability — now answers to a
single semantic helper instead of a hard-coded Pro string check.

The mechanic:
  - lib/plans.ts: isPayingTier(plan) returns true for trial,
    dream, maker, growth, pro (everything except canceled +
    null). Single source of truth for "this user can use the
    product."
  - 50 API routes had `if (client.plan !== "pro")` replaced with
    `if (!isPayingTier(client.plan))`. Error message updated from
    "X is a Pro feature." to "This feature requires an active
    subscription." — the new gate fires only for canceled users,
    so the message reflects reality.
  - 7 helper functions had `return plan === "growth" || plan ===
    "pro" || plan === "trial"` collapsed to `return isPayingTier(plan)`.
    Identical behavior, semantic naming.
  - 4 reports routes had `return plan === "pro"` (stricter Pro-only
    gate from Phase 7a) opened up — reports are exactly the
    differentiator that should NOT be Pro-only under the new
    positioning.
  - 4 dashboard.tsx functional gates updated for trial+paying.
  - app/integrations + app/reports upgrade-prompt copy reframed:
    "Pro feature" -> "Active subscription required" + "Every paid
    tier includes [feature]" to match the new pricing voice.

What stays Pro-only (correctly):
  - app/welcome-pro/page.tsx — Pro welcome flow + white-glove call
  - app/dashboard/page.tsx onboarding-call banner cluster (Pro
    service: same-day support + custom onboarding + quarterly
    check-ins)
  - app/api/gmail/route.ts + app/api/process/route.ts +
    app/help/gmail-setup/page.tsx — Gmail-related, already
    gated by FEATURES.GMAIL_INGEST anyway
  - app/billing/page.tsx downgrade-flow logic — addressed in
    commit 5 (billing page rewrite)
  - app/profitability/page.tsx isPro prop — visited in commit 5

Implementation note: a throwaway Node codemod did the bulk
transform (53 of 57 files). Initial run inserted the import
inside multi-line import destructures; fixed by tracking the line
ending `from "..."` rather than the opening `import {`. Script
was deleted after the sweep. Remaining 7 files (reports routes
with `isPlanAllowed` helpers, integrations + reports UI pages,
dashboard's trial-or-paying gates) edited by hand.

Verification: npx tsc --noEmit clean. Manual smoke-test deferred
to post-deploy (the visible behavioral surface is "previously-403
endpoints now return 200 for trial/dream/maker/growth users").

